      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Micah 4:8",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", of Mount Zion, the sense ‘hill’ rather than ‘tower’ appears well established. The margin of A.V., has here ‘secret place’ as also the LXX., but that seems to have come from connecting the word with a root of slightly different consonants (",
        "children": []
