        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "אפל",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " instead of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "עפל",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). The question arises: What hill is meant? And it appears best to understand it of some eminence near the house of Elisha. All Samaria was hilly in character (see ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Kings 16:24",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). The narrative by this allusion to a locality, as though it were well known, shews its historic character, and appears to go back in its early form to close upon the date of the events.",
        "children": []
      },
